def make_train_dataframe():
    
    train_data = pd.read_csv('train_data_extrafeat.csv',decimal=',')      #read csv file and make the dataframe
    train_data = train_data.drop(columns =['file']) #delete column file from the dataframe
    #get the id of each class  and add it in the dataframe
    label_encoder = LabelEncoder()
    classes = train_data.iloc[:, -2]                   #column class_name   
    label_encoder.fit(classes)
    class_id = label_encoder.transform(classes) 
    train_data['class_id'] = class_id
    train_data = train_data.drop(columns =['class_name'])
    train_data = train_data.replace(to_replace=['\[','\]'], value='',regex=True)
    return (train_data)



def make_test_dataframe():
    
    test_data = pd.read_csv('test_data_extrafeat.csv',decimal=',')      #read csv file and make the dataframe
    test_data = test_data.drop(columns =['file']) #delete column file from the dataframe
    #get the id of each class  and add it in the dataframe
    label_encoder = LabelEncoder()
    classes = test_data.iloc[:, -2]                   #column class_name   
    label_encoder.fit(classes)
    class_id = label_encoder.transform(classes) 
    test_data['class_id'] = class_id
    test_data = test_data.drop(columns =['class_name'])
    test_data = test_data.replace(to_replace=['\[','\]'], value='',regex=True)

    return (test_data)

def augmentation_data():
    augmentation_data = pd.read_csv('unused.csv',decimal=',')      #read csv file and make the dataframe
    augmentation_data = augmentation_data.drop(columns =['file']) #delete column file from the dataframe
    #get the id of each class  and add it in the dataframe
    label_encoder = LabelEncoder()
    classes = augmentation_data.iloc[:, -2]                   #column class_name   
    label_encoder.fit(classes)
    class_id = label_encoder.transform(classes) 
    augmentation_data['class_id'] = class_id
    augmentation_data = augmentation_data.drop(columns =['class_name'])
    augmentation_data = augmentation_data.replace(to_replace=['\[','\]'], value='',regex=True)
    
    return (augmentation_data)




def data_split(train_data,test_data):
    
    #scale and split the data into training and test sets
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    x_train = scaler.fit_transform(np.array(train_data.iloc[:, :-1], dtype = float))    #feauture matrix
    y_train = train_data['class_id']                                                    #labels id
    
    x_test = scaler.fit_transform(np.array(test_data.iloc[:, :-1], dtype = float))    #feauture matrix
    y_test = test_data['class_id']                                                    #labels id
    return(x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test)




def main():
    
    #make_csv_file()                             #the csv file is already made
    
    train1_data = make_train_dataframe()         #create the train dataframe
    train2_data = augmentation_data()
    train_data = pd.concat([train1_data,train2_data],ignore_index=True)
    
    test_data = make_test_dataframe()            #create the test dataframe
    
    x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = data_split(train_data,test_data)  #split the data into training and test sets
    return(x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test)

def build_model(x_train,y_train):                #function that builds our main architecture model
    
    lda = LinearDiscriminantAnalysis()
    lda.fit(x_train,y_train)
   
    
    x_train_lda = lda.transform(x_train)


    #neural network
    
    model = Sequential()
    
    model.add(Dense(512, activation= 'selu', input_shape= (x_train_lda.shape[1],)))
    model.add(Dropout(0.8,input_shape= (x_train_lda.shape[1],)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())

    model.add(Dense(256, activation='selu',kernel_initializer='lecun_normal'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5,input_shape= (x_train_lda.shape[1],)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    

    model.add(Dense(128, activation='selu',kernel_initializer='lecun_normal'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5,input_shape= (x_train_lda.shape[1],)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    

    model.add(Dense(128, activation='selu',kernel_initializer='lecun_normal'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5,input_shape= (x_train_lda.shape[1],)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    
    
    model.add(Dense(10, activation='softmax'))
    
    
    model.compile(loss="sparse_categorical_crossentropy", optimizer='Adam', metrics=['accuracy'],sample_weight_mode="temporal")
    
    model.summary()
    
    return(model)

def train_and_predict(model,x_train, x_eval, y_train, y_eval):
    
    lda = LinearDiscriminantAnalysis()
    lda.fit(x_train,y_train)
    lda.fit(x_eval,y_eval)
    
    x_train_lda = lda.transform(x_train)
    x_eval_lda = lda.transform(x_eval)

    checkpoint_filepath = '/Users/timkl/OneDrive/Υπολογιστής/trash'
    checkpoint = ModelCheckpoint(filepath=checkpoint_filepath,save_weights_only=True,monitor='val_accuracy',mode='max',save_best_only=True)
    es = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', mode='min',patience=30, verbose=1)

        
    history = model.fit(x_train_lda, y_train,validation_data = (x_eval_lda,y_eval), epochs=200, batch_size=64,callbacks=[es,checkpoint],verbose=2) #training_step

    model.load_weights(checkpoint_filepath)  # The model weights (that are considered the best) are loaded into the model.
    
    y_pred = model.predict(x_eval_lda)
    
    #Converting predictions to label
    pred = list()
    for i in range(len(y_pred)):
        pred.append(np.argmax(y_pred[i]))
            
            
    #model accuracy
    plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'])
    plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'])
    plt.title('Model accuracy')
    plt.ylabel('Accuracy')
    plt.xlabel('Epoch')
    plt.legend(['Train', 'Validation'], loc='upper left')
    plt.show()
    
    #model loss
    plt.plot(history.history['loss']) 
    plt.plot(history.history['val_loss']) 
    plt.title('Model loss') 
    plt.ylabel('Loss') 
    plt.xlabel('Epoch') 
    plt.legend(['Train', 'Validation'], loc='upper left') 
    plt.show()
        
        
        
    return (pred)

    model2.add(Dense(256, activation='relu',kernel_initializer='lecun_normal'))

    model2.add(BatchNormalization())
    

    model2.add(Dense(128, activation='relu',kernel_initializer='lecun_normal'))

def show_test_results(y_test,pred):           #classification report metric
    
        
        
    a = accuracy_score(y_test,pred)
    print('Accuracy is:', a*100)
    labels = ['airport','bus','metro','metro_station','park','public_square','shopping_mall','street_pedestrian','street_traffic','tram']
    report = classification_report(y_test, pred,target_names =labels)
    print("Classification Report")
    print(report)
    
    
    confusion = confusion_matrix(y_test, pred)
    show_cm(confusion,labels)
    
    
    
    
def show_cm(cm,labels):                       #confusion matrix metric 
    
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(9,9))
    plt.imshow(cm, interpolation='nearest', cmap=plt.cm.Blues)
    plt.title("Confusion matrix")
    plt.colorbar()
    tick_marks = np.arange(len(labels))
    plt.xticks(tick_marks, labels, rotation=25)
    plt.yticks(tick_marks, labels)
            
    cm = cm.astype('float') / cm.sum(axis=1)[:, np.newaxis]
            
    thresh = cm.max() / 2.
    for i, j in itertools.product(range(cm.shape[0]), range(cm.shape[1])):
        plt.text(j, i, round(cm[i, j], 3),
        horizontalalignment="center",
        color="white" if cm[i, j] > thresh else "black")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.ylabel('True label')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted label')
    plt.show()
